# Patterns from sensitive-patterns.list that should also match by DIRECTORY NAME
# (in addition to basename). One pattern per line. Lines starting with '#' and blank lines
# are ignored. Compared after stripping leading '**/' (mirroring the bash-consumer convention
# in sensitive-patterns.list).
#
# This file is ASCII; do not save with a UTF-8 BOM.
# Patterns with '#' inside the pattern body are treated literally by consumers; do not use
# inline comments on pattern lines.
#
# Effect: when the bridge builds the find expression for these patterns, it emits both
# -iname AND -ipath '*/<pattern>*/*' arms. Patterns NOT listed here keep basename-only
# behavior unless they are bilateral '*X*' patterns, which continue to emit both arms.

credentials*
bearer_*
